p: The attack rate was null for both species, except with Ae. aegypti for Cairns, Darwin, Rockhampton, Thursday Island, and Townsville ranging from 0.1 to 3 for the ‘worst-‘case scenario ( Table 2). The biggest AR for the ‘worst-‘case scenario was in Darwin followed by Cairns and Rockhampton. Our results show, to a certain extent, that reducing the mosquito population together with a longer EIP would only partly prevent transmission (or contain an outbreak).
